Jeffrey Fontana Memorial
Artist: Gary Alsum
2004

This artwork was commissioned to commemorate Jeffrey Fontana, the young San Jose police officer killed in the line of duty.  Mr. Fontana was a 24-year-old Woodside resident and rookie police officer patrolling the upscale Almaden Valley neighborhood when he was fatally shot during a routine stop. 


    
        
